1
00:00:20,709 --> 00:00:23,709
THE SOFT SKIN

2
00:01:14,501 --> 00:01:16,626
CROSSING

3
00:01:36,209 --> 00:01:38,751
I just called your office.

4
00:01:38,917 --> 00:01:42,959
The subway broke down, not a cab in sight.

5
00:01:43,126 --> 00:01:44,376
- Hello, Odile.
- Hello, Pierre.

6
00:01:44,542 --> 00:01:47,126
- What's your departure time?
- I've got 40 minutes.

7
00:01:47,292 --> 00:01:49,292
In this traffic? Never!

8
00:01:49,751 --> 00:01:53,001
- I must try it, Franca.
- I've packed your suitcase.

9
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:55,292
- Hello, Daddy!
- Hello, princess.

10
00:01:55,459 --> 00:01:59,542
- Will you take the car?
- If you come along to park it.

11
00:01:59,709 --> 00:02:03,292
Only if you do the driving.
I make you too nervous.

12
00:02:07,501 --> 00:02:08,542
It's my husband.

13
00:02:08,626 --> 00:02:11,292
- It's a tie rack.
- Stop kidding.

14
00:02:11,459 --> 00:02:13,167
What's up?

15
00:02:13,334 --> 00:02:15,876
Pierre's late. He's lecturing in Lisbon.

16
00:02:16,042 --> 00:02:18,501
- I can drive you.
- Franca will do it.

17
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:22,167
Go ahead, you're a much better driver.

18
00:02:22,334 --> 00:02:24,126
That's right, he is.

19
00:02:27,751 --> 00:02:28,834
Bye, princess.

20
00:02:28,917 --> 00:02:30,251
Bye, Daddy.

21
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:31,959
Be good now.

22
00:02:32,751 --> 00:02:35,001
Can I ride to the airport?

23
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:36,792
You know you can't.

24
00:02:36,959 --> 00:02:39,417
Why not? She'll enjoy it.

25
00:02:39,501 --> 00:02:40,542
Okay, you can come.

26
00:02:40,626 --> 00:02:45,084
Mademoiselle,
would you get Sabine's coat, please?

27
00:02:45,501 --> 00:02:47,876
Call to tell me where you are staying.

28
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:49,876
Here's an article about you.

29
00:02:50,042 --> 00:02:52,042
I'll read it later.

30
00:02:52,376 --> 00:02:55,834
Please be careful.
He can always catch another plane.

31
00:03:12,626 --> 00:03:14,376
- What's the time?
- It's 3:45.

32
00:03:14,542 --> 00:03:17,417
We'll never make it.

33
00:03:17,584 --> 00:03:19,917
Is your talk on Stendhal?

34
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:21,709
No, on Balzac.

35
00:03:29,584 --> 00:03:32,001
There's a speed limit, but what the hell.

36
00:03:35,292 --> 00:03:37,501
A cop! If he's after us, we're sunk.

37
00:03:41,126 --> 00:03:43,251
You just leave it to me.

38
00:04:02,209 --> 00:04:04,167
Bye, Michel. Thanks.

39
00:04:04,334 --> 00:04:06,001
- Porter?
- No thanks.

40
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:12,626
The Lisbon plane, can I still make it?

41
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:16,084
I'm not sure...

42
00:04:18,209 --> 00:04:20,876
Mr Lachenay for the Lisbon flight?

43
00:04:21,042 --> 00:04:23,876
<i>Let me check.</i>

44
00:04:24,584 --> 00:04:26,709
They might have taken the ladder away.

45
00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:29,542
<i>Check in Mr Lachenay's luggage.</i>

46
00:04:30,876 --> 00:04:32,626
This way, please. Let's hurry.

47
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:45,084
They're taking the ladder away.

48
00:04:47,459 --> 00:04:48,876
No, it's going back.

49
00:05:00,209 --> 00:05:01,959
Let's hurry.

50
00:05:06,667 --> 00:05:08,167
Quick, the door!

51
00:05:33,417 --> 00:05:38,376
<i>Please fasten your seat belt,
and no smoking. Thank you.</i>

52
00:05:43,751 --> 00:05:45,876
Seats forward, please.

53
00:07:20,751 --> 00:07:22,626
Will you wait here, please?

54
00:07:26,251 --> 00:07:28,001
We can go now.

55
00:07:31,792 --> 00:07:34,667
A photo with the stewardess, please.

56
00:07:52,751 --> 00:07:54,334
This way, Mr Lachenay.

57
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,251
Here's the bathroom.

58
00:08:13,417 --> 00:08:14,584
Fine.

59
00:08:19,001 --> 00:08:20,042
Perfect.

60
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,334
For you.

61
00:08:55,542 --> 00:08:57,501
BALZAC AND MONEY

62
00:08:57,667 --> 00:09:01,042
Why Balzac and money?

63
00:09:01,209 --> 00:09:05,626
Well, I'm a fan of Balzac's
and I don't despise money.

64
00:09:06,376 --> 00:09:11,959
But all joking aside, that happens to be
the title of one of my books.

65
00:09:12,126 --> 00:09:15,751
How about a book on Balzac and love?

66
00:09:16,167 --> 00:09:17,376
Why not?

67
00:09:17,792 --> 00:09:20,459
There's a full house.

68
00:09:27,251 --> 00:09:29,126
We'll need some extra seats.

69
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:33,126
- What's Ionesco up to?
- He's doing fine.

70
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:37,459
- We'd better go now.
- I'm ready.

71
00:09:40,917 --> 00:09:42,709
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

72
00:09:47,626 --> 00:09:51,459
As soon as I am through
with the introduction...

73
00:09:51,834 --> 00:09:55,292
I know what to do. See you later.

74
00:09:59,584 --> 00:10:01,334
<i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

75
00:10:04,042 --> 00:10:07,792
<i>We've got a small problem
with the microphone.</i>

76
00:10:07,959 --> 00:10:10,876
<i>I present you Pierre Lachenay.</i>

77
00:10:18,709 --> 00:10:20,959
How about lunch tomorrow?

78
00:10:21,126 --> 00:10:23,209
Sorry, I leave at noon.

79
00:10:23,376 --> 00:10:24,751
What a pity.

80
00:10:25,042 --> 00:10:26,834
Look, it's Pierre Lachenay.

81
00:10:27,917 --> 00:10:32,376
We hope to see you in Paris very soon.
Goodbye.

82
00:11:05,709 --> 00:11:08,084
Here's where I get off.

83
00:11:10,001 --> 00:11:11,209
I'll call you.

84
00:11:11,376 --> 00:11:12,709
Yes, tomorrow.

85
00:11:30,376 --> 00:11:32,834
I forgot to ask you your floor...

86
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:34,376
That's quite all right.

87
00:11:43,209 --> 00:11:45,084
I'm sorry.

88
00:11:48,334 --> 00:11:49,667
Thank you, sir.

89
00:13:45,501 --> 00:13:47,876
Would you ring room 813?

90
00:13:48,042 --> 00:13:50,292
<i>Hold on.</i>

91
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:57,501
Hello, room 813?

92
00:13:58,792 --> 00:14:02,209
Miss, I was in the elevator with you...

93
00:14:02,376 --> 00:14:04,542
I wanted to apologise...

94
00:14:04,709 --> 00:14:06,876
<i>Apologise for what?</i>

95
00:14:07,501 --> 00:14:09,626
You got off at the 8th floor...

96
00:14:09,792 --> 00:14:11,376
<i>Of course.</i>

97
00:14:11,542 --> 00:14:14,584
Well, since I'd past my floor anyway,

98
00:14:14,959 --> 00:14:17,667
and you had so many packages,

99
00:14:18,417 --> 00:14:21,126
I should have helped you with them.

100
00:14:21,292 --> 00:14:24,876
<i>Not at all. That's perfectly all right.</i>

101
00:14:26,001 --> 00:14:29,209
Well, forgive me.

102
00:14:30,042 --> 00:14:32,292
Look, I wonder...
Could we have a drink together?

103
00:14:32,459 --> 00:14:33,834
<i>Right now?</i>

104
00:14:34,001 --> 00:14:35,501
Yes, right now.

105
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:37,501
<i>Do you know what time it is?</i>

106
00:14:38,917 --> 00:14:40,376
Oh, it's past 1 a.m.

107
00:14:40,542 --> 00:14:42,501
<i>And the bar's closed.</i>

108
00:14:44,084 --> 00:14:46,751
Then, could we have a drink tomorrow?

109
00:14:46,917 --> 00:14:50,251
<i>There's really no point, you know.</i>

110
00:14:50,417 --> 00:14:52,209
I see. I'm very sorry...

111
00:14:54,709 --> 00:14:56,834
Good night. Please excuse me.

112
00:15:26,709 --> 00:15:31,709
<i>Look, I didn't mean to be so rude.
It was very kind of you to call me.</i>

113
00:15:31,917 --> 00:15:34,126
<i>Let's have that drink together.</i>

114
00:15:34,292 --> 00:15:37,084
Fine. In the morning?

115
00:15:37,251 --> 00:15:40,084
<i>No, I've got to go shopping.</i>

116
00:15:40,251 --> 00:15:43,042
<i>Can we make it in the afternoon?</i>

117
00:15:43,751 --> 00:15:44,959
Yes, of course.

118
00:15:45,126 --> 00:15:47,584
<i>In the bar at 6:00?</i>

119
00:15:47,751 --> 00:15:49,042
All right.

120
00:15:49,209 --> 00:15:51,626
- <i>Good night.</i>
- You too.

121
00:16:28,626 --> 00:16:31,501
Do you enjoy your work,
or do you dislike it?

122
00:16:33,001 --> 00:16:34,584
I like my job.

123
00:16:34,751 --> 00:16:36,459
I started a year ago.

124
00:16:36,626 --> 00:16:39,459
They said I'd soon be fed up.

125
00:16:39,876 --> 00:16:41,042
Maybe.

126
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:44,542
Many girls do quit after a few years.

127
00:16:44,709 --> 00:16:46,251
What happens to them?

128
00:16:47,376 --> 00:16:48,709
They get married.

129
00:16:49,584 --> 00:16:52,959
I love my parents...

130
00:16:53,126 --> 00:16:56,376
They live in Bordeaux.

131
00:16:56,542 --> 00:16:58,292
That's where I'm from.

132
00:17:02,417 --> 00:17:08,751
Papa used to say it's a job for a snob,
but now he doesn't mind.

133
00:17:11,126 --> 00:17:13,459
- Don't you know her?
- Yes, I do.

134
00:17:14,209 --> 00:17:17,042
They're friends of mine.

135
00:17:17,209 --> 00:17:23,542
That's Frank.
He's the co-pilot of the plane you came on.

136
00:17:28,251 --> 00:17:31,042
We almost met six months ago.

137
00:17:31,209 --> 00:17:32,334
What do you mean?

138
00:17:32,709 --> 00:17:37,751
I knew a TV writer
who worked with Louise de Vilmorin.

139
00:17:37,917 --> 00:17:41,334
She had us to dinner once.
You were expected.

140
00:17:42,376 --> 00:17:45,167
We waited, but you never showed up.

141
00:17:45,334 --> 00:17:47,459
I just couldn't help it.

142
00:17:47,876 --> 00:17:51,042
I haven't read all of your books.
In fact, I haven't read any.

143
00:17:51,209 --> 00:17:55,834
But I've seen you on television.

144
00:17:56,167 --> 00:18:01,001
So, at the airport, I recognised you.

145
00:18:02,292 --> 00:18:06,334
So Balzac decides
to put out a novel a month.

146
00:18:06,501 --> 00:18:10,751
Not slim ones, mind you, but huge volumes.

147
00:18:10,917 --> 00:18:12,834
He writes a chapter a day.

148
00:18:13,001 --> 00:18:16,917
He can't live on what the publishers pay him,

149
00:18:17,084 --> 00:18:20,376
so he buys his own printing plant.

150
00:18:20,542 --> 00:18:25,876
But business is bad,
and his partners pull out.

151
00:18:26,126 --> 00:18:29,626
He decides to do it all by himself,

152
00:18:29,792 --> 00:18:32,459
casting his own type,

153
00:18:32,626 --> 00:18:34,292
setting it himself,

154
00:18:34,459 --> 00:18:38,084
even making his own paper.

155
00:18:38,251 --> 00:18:42,917
But he loses everything,
including Madame de Berny's money.

156
00:18:43,084 --> 00:18:44,542
Wasn't she his mistress?

157
00:18:44,709 --> 00:18:48,084
Yes. I'll tell you how that came to pass.

158
00:18:48,792 --> 00:18:52,542
Madame de Balzac wants
a wife for her son, HonorГ©.

159
00:18:52,917 --> 00:18:56,042
Madame de Berny
has two daughters to marry off.

160
00:18:56,209 --> 00:19:00,042
HonorГ© meets the two young girls,

161
00:19:00,209 --> 00:19:02,292
who leave him cold.

162
00:19:02,459 --> 00:19:05,084
But he falls in love with the mother.

163
00:19:05,459 --> 00:19:06,667
That's marvellous!

164
00:19:09,792 --> 00:19:12,667
I've been talking for hours.

165
00:19:12,834 --> 00:19:14,876
It was fascinating!

166
00:19:15,042 --> 00:19:18,334
I'll lend you some books, if you'd like.

167
00:19:18,501 --> 00:19:21,042
I didn't realise it was getting so late!

168
00:19:21,251 --> 00:19:23,501
Look how kind these folks are.

169
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:27,501
In France, the boss would have
put us out hours ago.

170
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:30,876
I'll ask for the bill.
It must be daylight by now.

171
00:22:21,709 --> 00:22:23,667
Coming, Madame.

172
00:22:32,584 --> 00:22:33,792
Matches?

173
00:23:54,417 --> 00:23:56,126
- Surprised?
- A little.

174
00:23:56,292 --> 00:23:58,251
It was easy.

175
00:23:58,417 --> 00:24:01,167
I called your secretary,
then your Lisbon hotel,

176
00:24:01,334 --> 00:24:05,251
checked with the airport, and here I am!

177
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,959
Michel and Odile are coming over later.

178
00:24:12,126 --> 00:24:15,251
I knew you'd be tired
but it was only possible today.

179
00:24:16,834 --> 00:24:18,542
They are going to Japan.

180
00:24:21,709 --> 00:24:24,334
How does one turn off this heater?

181
00:24:31,834 --> 00:24:34,584
I guess we can turn that off.

182
00:24:36,709 --> 00:24:39,751
- I hate sports programs.
- So do I.

183
00:24:40,626 --> 00:24:44,667
The other day,
on the way back from the airport,

184
00:24:45,376 --> 00:24:48,209
my car broke down on Saint-Denis Street.

185
00:24:48,459 --> 00:24:50,709
What were you doing there?

186
00:24:51,084 --> 00:24:52,584
Tell us all about it.

187
00:24:53,334 --> 00:24:55,042
Not Saint-Martin, Saint-Denis.

188
00:24:55,209 --> 00:24:58,709
I was just going to the Japanese art shop.

189
00:24:58,876 --> 00:25:01,167
To buy some prints, I suppose.

190
00:25:01,334 --> 00:25:03,042
You guessed right.

191
00:25:05,251 --> 00:25:07,292
I meant to ask you...

192
00:25:07,751 --> 00:25:09,542
- Ice cream?
- Yes, please.

193
00:25:09,709 --> 00:25:11,667
Where you stay in Tokyo?

194
00:25:11,834 --> 00:25:14,167
The Takanawa Hotel is pretty good.

195
00:25:14,667 --> 00:25:16,376
- Listen.
- What is it?

196
00:25:17,834 --> 00:25:18,876
That's Sabine.

197
00:25:19,001 --> 00:25:20,501
I'll go this time.

198
00:25:20,834 --> 00:25:22,376
Is it your first trip to Japan?

199
00:25:22,542 --> 00:25:25,376
No, I already went there two years ago.

200
00:25:25,542 --> 00:25:29,501
As soon as you put a cigarette
in your mouth, a woman lights it up.

201
00:25:35,834 --> 00:25:37,626
What are you doing?

202
00:25:40,501 --> 00:25:43,751
I'm looking for my book.

203
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:47,251
It's late. You should be fast asleep.

204
00:25:47,417 --> 00:25:49,042
I have slept.

205
00:25:49,209 --> 00:25:50,917
Yes, but not enough.

206
00:25:54,209 --> 00:25:56,001
Back to bed, now.

207
00:25:57,376 --> 00:25:58,751
Here.

208
00:25:59,917 --> 00:26:01,292
And here.

209
00:26:05,126 --> 00:26:06,917
That's enough, now.

210
00:26:08,792 --> 00:26:10,084
I'm closing the door.

211
00:26:10,251 --> 00:26:12,084
Open it more.

212
00:26:12,209 --> 00:26:13,376
Is that enough?

213
00:26:13,459 --> 00:26:14,792
A bit more.

214
00:26:14,959 --> 00:26:17,167
No more than this.

215
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:10,917
They're going.
You might at least say goodbye.

216
00:27:13,251 --> 00:27:15,292
So you're off to Tokyo?

217
00:27:15,459 --> 00:27:17,917
Not yet. They are leaving next month.

218
00:27:19,126 --> 00:27:21,251
See you at Suzanne's tomorrow.

219
00:27:21,417 --> 00:27:22,876
Let's go together.

220
00:27:23,042 --> 00:27:24,959
We'll see. I'll call you.

221
00:27:25,126 --> 00:27:27,542
I can rely on you to call.

222
00:27:30,001 --> 00:27:31,167
Have a good trip back.

223
00:27:31,251 --> 00:27:32,292
Goodbye.

224
00:27:41,376 --> 00:27:42,459
Were you bored?

225
00:27:42,584 --> 00:27:43,959
No, I like them.

226
00:27:44,126 --> 00:27:45,417
They're nice.

227
00:27:47,084 --> 00:27:50,626
By the way, Kanayan called. He's furious.

228
00:27:51,209 --> 00:27:52,292
Again?

229
00:27:52,417 --> 00:27:55,292
What is it this time?

230
00:27:56,584 --> 00:27:59,917
It seems that in the latest edition,

231
00:28:00,084 --> 00:28:02,376
his article was put in last place.

232
00:28:02,542 --> 00:28:05,917
He said, "I know it's petty",

233
00:28:06,084 --> 00:28:09,501
"but as I'm from an underdeveloped country,"

234
00:28:11,334 --> 00:28:15,084
"I've got a terrible inferiority complex."

235
00:28:16,501 --> 00:28:19,251
I felt like quoting that joke...

236
00:28:19,417 --> 00:28:23,501
"That's no complex, my dear,
you're really inferior!"

237
00:28:25,626 --> 00:28:27,292
But that would be going too far.

238
00:28:27,542 --> 00:28:31,376
Once you know him, he's really a nice guy.

239
00:28:34,292 --> 00:28:36,792
Pierre LACHENAY, President
5th floor, left

240
00:28:39,251 --> 00:28:42,084
- What about that call?
- The line's busy.

241
00:28:43,917 --> 00:28:45,542
Can we do the mail now?

242
00:28:45,917 --> 00:28:46,959
If you like.

243
00:28:55,501 --> 00:28:58,167
For Mr Kanayan, 17 Street so-and-so.

244
00:28:59,209 --> 00:29:00,667
My dear Kanayan.

245
00:29:01,001 --> 00:29:05,084
You're decision to stop writing for us

246
00:29:06,334 --> 00:29:09,209
is due to a misunderstanding...

247
00:29:11,001 --> 00:29:13,209
No. I'll lunch with him instead.

248
00:29:13,376 --> 00:29:15,001
- And the other letters?
- Later.

249
00:29:15,167 --> 00:29:16,834
What about the calls?

250
00:29:17,834 --> 00:29:20,042
I'll take these if they call back.

251
00:29:20,209 --> 00:29:21,376
So I'm not calling anyone?

252
00:29:21,542 --> 00:29:22,876
No one else.

253
00:29:24,126 --> 00:29:25,709
And your appointment?

254
00:29:25,876 --> 00:29:27,709
Yes, I remember.

255
00:29:56,042 --> 00:29:58,209
- I'm going out.
- And your appointment?

256
00:29:58,376 --> 00:29:59,542
I'll be right back.

257
00:30:14,751 --> 00:30:19,084
When you called, I was on my way out.

258
00:30:19,667 --> 00:30:20,959
When's a good time?

259
00:30:21,126 --> 00:30:24,251
It's hard to say. My hours are so crazy.

260
00:30:24,501 --> 00:30:27,251
I lose many friends that way.

261
00:30:27,417 --> 00:30:30,917
People invite me, but they are never sure

262
00:30:31,084 --> 00:30:34,251
I'll turn up, so they stop asking me.

263
00:30:34,417 --> 00:30:36,334
Well, I'll never stop.

264
00:30:36,501 --> 00:30:40,251
I'll always be there whenever you need me.

265
00:30:40,417 --> 00:30:41,959
God, it's windy!

266
00:30:42,584 --> 00:30:45,126
Do you have to go to the gym?

267
00:30:45,292 --> 00:30:48,334
It's part of the refresher course.

268
00:30:48,501 --> 00:30:50,376
What's that?

269
00:30:51,209 --> 00:30:54,209
We practise first aid, safety drills

270
00:30:54,501 --> 00:30:58,334
and how to handle lifeboats.

271
00:30:58,542 --> 00:31:00,459
It's late, I must run.

272
00:31:26,167 --> 00:31:28,626
- Guess what I've got!
- Something for me?

273
00:31:28,792 --> 00:31:30,584
It's a record.

274
00:31:31,834 --> 00:31:33,376
A little girl singing?

275
00:31:33,542 --> 00:31:35,459
No, something nicer.

276
00:31:36,501 --> 00:31:38,667
Haydn's Toy Symphony.

277
00:31:38,834 --> 00:31:42,542
You hear toys and birds calls in the music.

278
00:31:43,876 --> 00:31:45,001
Wait and listen.

279
00:31:56,126 --> 00:31:57,501
It's lovely.

280
00:32:07,251 --> 00:32:10,001
Where's the paper that was here?

281
00:32:10,167 --> 00:32:12,126
I didn't touch it.

282
00:32:13,542 --> 00:32:15,459
It's not here and I need it!

283
00:32:15,626 --> 00:32:18,167
Let's see if it's up there.

284
00:32:18,334 --> 00:32:23,501
It had a book review I meant to keep.

285
00:32:24,042 --> 00:32:25,667
I'm sure it's around.

286
00:32:30,626 --> 00:32:32,126
Here it is.

287
00:32:33,209 --> 00:32:36,209
This isn't the one, God damn it!

288
00:32:36,376 --> 00:32:38,584
Calm down.

289
00:32:38,751 --> 00:32:40,917
Our news dealer can get it for you.

290
00:32:41,084 --> 00:32:43,126
I want it right now!

291
00:32:43,292 --> 00:32:47,167
Is that so?
Well, get your lousy paper yourself!

292
00:34:27,667 --> 00:34:29,834
I love you.

293
00:34:31,126 --> 00:34:34,001
Ever since knowing you,
I've become a new man,

294
00:34:34,542 --> 00:34:38,209
one who cannot conceive
of living without you. I love you.

295
00:34:43,251 --> 00:34:45,126
Are you coming or going?

296
00:34:45,834 --> 00:34:49,042
We take off in half an hour.

297
00:34:49,792 --> 00:34:52,209
I'm taking the bus. Are you coming with me?

298
00:34:53,584 --> 00:34:57,042
Catherine, please, I've got to see someone.

299
00:34:57,584 --> 00:34:59,876
All right, bye.

300
00:35:07,001 --> 00:35:08,584
You're still here?

301
00:35:09,584 --> 00:35:13,959
I saw a plane take off
and assumed you were on it.

302
00:35:14,876 --> 00:35:17,417
Lots of planes take off from here, you know.

303
00:35:18,584 --> 00:35:21,042
They're changing a wheel,

304
00:35:21,501 --> 00:35:23,209
so we're delayed.

305
00:36:14,542 --> 00:36:15,751
Are you asleep?

306
00:36:22,251 --> 00:36:23,376
You're mean!

307
00:36:38,084 --> 00:36:40,876
I'm sorry I carried on so about that paper.

308
00:36:41,084 --> 00:36:44,334
It wasn't that urgent.

309
00:36:44,709 --> 00:36:47,751
Besides, I found it 10 minutes later.

310
00:37:02,709 --> 00:37:05,251
Let's go away for a few days.

311
00:37:06,126 --> 00:37:09,834
We haven't been alone together for years.

312
00:37:10,167 --> 00:37:12,917
Sabine could stay with Odile.

313
00:37:13,751 --> 00:37:15,376
What do you think?

314
00:37:16,126 --> 00:37:18,167
A few days in the country?

315
00:37:19,959 --> 00:37:21,876
Maybe. We'll see.

316
00:37:38,751 --> 00:37:41,542
Hello, Mr Lachenay.
How is Madame Lachenay?

317
00:37:41,709 --> 00:37:43,001
She's fine.

318
00:38:03,834 --> 00:38:05,292
The menu.

319
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:18,667
- Did you wait for me yesterday?
- Yes, you were late.

320
00:38:18,834 --> 00:38:19,917
What happened?

321
00:38:20,084 --> 00:38:23,167
A snowstorm in Frankfurt. I'm sorry.

322
00:38:23,334 --> 00:38:27,334
Next time we're held up, I could cable you.

323
00:38:27,501 --> 00:38:28,917
Or call my office.

324
00:38:29,084 --> 00:38:31,209
What about your secretary?

325
00:38:31,376 --> 00:38:33,001
It doesn't matter.

326
00:38:33,167 --> 00:38:34,917
I didn't expect you.

327
00:38:35,042 --> 00:38:36,084
Glad?

328
00:38:36,167 --> 00:38:38,167
Yes, I was feeling blue.

329
00:38:38,626 --> 00:38:42,959
Here's a present.
You can use it to make notes

330
00:38:43,126 --> 00:38:45,292
during your lectures.

331
00:38:45,459 --> 00:38:47,042
Thank you.

332
00:38:47,542 --> 00:38:49,334
I'm most pleased.

333
00:38:56,751 --> 00:39:00,667
Can I sleep at your place?
I'm not expected home.

334
00:39:01,959 --> 00:39:05,292
Look, I hate to say no,

335
00:39:05,459 --> 00:39:07,584
but I'm scared

336
00:39:08,417 --> 00:39:10,292
of the concierge.

337
00:39:10,417 --> 00:39:15,584
Besides, the landlady's
an old friend of my parents.

338
00:39:16,334 --> 00:39:20,126
No one's ever spent the night there.
We can't.

339
00:39:21,626 --> 00:39:23,001
Don't be angry.

340
00:39:23,334 --> 00:39:25,584
I want to stay with you, too.

341
00:39:25,834 --> 00:39:27,709
I understand.

342
00:39:29,584 --> 00:39:32,209
Why don't we sleep some place else?

343
00:39:32,376 --> 00:39:35,751
All right. First, I'll pick up a dress.

344
00:39:36,584 --> 00:39:38,792
Then, a nice restaurant.

345
00:39:38,959 --> 00:39:41,251
A place where we can dance?

346
00:39:41,417 --> 00:39:43,959
Choose a place.

347
00:39:47,334 --> 00:39:49,667
I warn you, I don't dance.

348
00:39:50,209 --> 00:39:52,001
I never learned how.

349
00:39:52,792 --> 00:39:56,001
Even when you were... I mean...

350
00:39:56,167 --> 00:39:59,001
Yes, even when I was young.

351
00:39:59,584 --> 00:40:02,209
That made it hard to find a wife.

352
00:40:02,376 --> 00:40:03,751
Don't be silly!

353
00:40:04,959 --> 00:40:08,292
Go ahead, dance.

354
00:40:08,459 --> 00:40:09,917
What will you do?

355
00:40:10,084 --> 00:40:11,917
I'll just look at you.

356
00:40:12,251 --> 00:40:14,167
That will be my pleasure.

357
00:41:08,626 --> 00:41:12,084
LUXURY STUDIOS
OPEN 24 HOURS A DAY

358
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:45,834
- A room please.
- No reservation?

359
00:41:46,417 --> 00:41:50,542
Sorry, not now.

360
00:41:54,084 --> 00:41:55,626
You can go upstairs.

361
00:41:58,917 --> 00:42:02,084
But I'll have a room in 15 minutes.
Can you wait?

362
00:42:02,792 --> 00:42:04,417
Fifteen minutes?

363
00:42:09,042 --> 00:42:11,751
Please, Pierre, let's go.

364
00:42:12,042 --> 00:42:13,084
Of course.

365
00:42:30,292 --> 00:42:32,876
Disappointed?

366
00:42:33,084 --> 00:42:34,959
No, I felt the same way.

367
00:42:35,709 --> 00:42:37,792
I'd no idea it would be so sordid.

368
00:42:38,876 --> 00:42:41,292
We need a place of our own.

369
00:42:42,834 --> 00:42:44,501
I'll take you home.

370
00:43:13,001 --> 00:43:15,709
- I'm off now.
- One more kiss.

371
00:43:24,542 --> 00:43:26,084
Listen.

372
00:43:26,542 --> 00:43:29,834
We'll be careful. Come on up.

373
00:43:30,084 --> 00:43:31,126
Come.

374
00:43:47,126 --> 00:43:50,251
I'll go first.

375
00:43:50,417 --> 00:43:53,876
It's too risky.

376
00:43:54,042 --> 00:43:55,876
You'd be worried.

377
00:43:56,042 --> 00:43:58,209
There's another way. When do you leave?

378
00:43:59,042 --> 00:44:02,209
In two days. I'll be back Monday.

379
00:44:02,834 --> 00:44:07,834
Next week, I've got a lecture in Reims.
You'll come along.

380
00:44:08,001 --> 00:44:12,251
We'll have two whole days on our own.

381
00:44:12,417 --> 00:44:14,126
That'll be wonderful.

382
00:44:14,292 --> 00:44:16,334
Paris is no good for us.

383
00:44:16,501 --> 00:44:19,376
Yes, you're right.

384
00:44:22,542 --> 00:44:23,834
Think of me.

385
00:44:31,167 --> 00:44:32,959
Where are you going now?

386
00:44:33,209 --> 00:44:34,417
Home.

387
00:44:34,709 --> 00:44:37,084
I'll tell my wife I just got back.

388
00:44:39,709 --> 00:44:42,251
I don't want you to go there.

389
00:45:13,959 --> 00:45:15,042
What's the matter?

390
00:45:15,417 --> 00:45:18,376
Just looking at your blue jeans.

391
00:45:19,959 --> 00:45:21,084
You disapprove?

392
00:45:21,876 --> 00:45:26,251
Well, I prefer you in dresses.
Did you bring any?

393
00:45:26,542 --> 00:45:27,584
Of course.

394
00:45:28,626 --> 00:45:30,042
Great.

395
00:45:30,917 --> 00:45:32,001
We need gas.

396
00:45:32,584 --> 00:45:33,626
Here?

397
00:45:49,834 --> 00:45:51,667
Fill it up, please.

398
00:47:02,751 --> 00:47:04,042
50 francs.

399
00:47:52,834 --> 00:47:56,834
Look at your picture!

400
00:47:59,626 --> 00:48:02,917
Are you giving a lecture in Reims?

401
00:48:03,292 --> 00:48:08,001
No, I'm to present a film AllГ©gret
made before Andre Gide's death.

402
00:48:08,834 --> 00:48:13,251
I accepted only so that we can have
two days together.

403
00:48:16,001 --> 00:48:19,959
Look up the hotels in Reims.

404
00:48:28,876 --> 00:48:30,917
The Grand Hotel's the best.

405
00:48:31,417 --> 00:48:33,792
The sponsors will be at that one.

406
00:48:34,334 --> 00:48:35,584
What's next?

407
00:48:35,959 --> 00:48:39,459
Next, The Lion d'Or.

408
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:44,209
That might be risky too.

409
00:48:46,501 --> 00:48:48,584
The Michelet just has rooms.

410
00:48:48,751 --> 00:48:51,792
We can eat out. Where is it?

411
00:48:53,292 --> 00:48:55,501
It's Place Michelet in Reims.

412
00:48:55,584 --> 00:48:57,084
A room for two.

413
00:48:57,251 --> 00:49:01,792
Did you make a reservation?
Number 12 is a double.

414
00:49:01,959 --> 00:49:03,792
Does it have a bathroom? We'll take it.

415
00:49:03,959 --> 00:49:05,834
Any luggage? I'll show you the way.

416
00:49:18,709 --> 00:49:21,042
Excuse me, Madame. I'll go first.

417
00:49:26,251 --> 00:49:29,209
It's very quiet here.

418
00:49:29,376 --> 00:49:31,167
Thank you. That's for you.

419
00:49:32,751 --> 00:49:36,376
A nice little room. Michelet's a good name.

420
00:49:36,542 --> 00:49:39,376
I'd better unpack and bathe.

421
00:49:39,876 --> 00:49:42,084
There goes my last pair!

422
00:49:42,251 --> 00:49:48,417
I'd better run over
and let them know I'm here.

423
00:49:48,667 --> 00:49:50,542
I won't be long.

424
00:49:50,709 --> 00:49:54,626
I need stockings and a ticket for tonight.

425
00:50:20,376 --> 00:50:23,334
<i>Don't forget my stockings!</i>

426
00:50:24,709 --> 00:50:27,376
- Hello, sir. Any luggage?
- No luggage.

427
00:50:32,876 --> 00:50:36,042
- Your suite is all ready.
- No need, I can't stay.

428
00:50:36,209 --> 00:50:37,751
We'll take care of your luggage.

429
00:50:37,917 --> 00:50:40,001
- Do you want to rest?
- I'm not staying.

430
00:50:41,001 --> 00:50:43,209
- How are you, old man?
- Fine and you?

431
00:50:43,376 --> 00:50:45,917
Want to freshen up first?

432
00:50:46,084 --> 00:50:47,626
I'm all right.

433
00:50:47,792 --> 00:50:51,959
When I invited you, I was sure you'd refuse.

434
00:50:52,126 --> 00:50:55,292
But they know we're friends, so I had to try.

435
00:50:55,459 --> 00:50:56,876
Is your wife here?

436
00:50:57,042 --> 00:50:58,209
She's in Paris.

437
00:50:58,376 --> 00:50:59,542
Give her my best.

438
00:50:59,709 --> 00:51:02,376
Let me introduce you.

439
00:51:02,542 --> 00:51:05,209
Father Cote, our welfare chairman.

440
00:51:05,542 --> 00:51:06,626
Pleased to meet you.

441
00:51:06,792 --> 00:51:09,751
Mr Bertrand, our theatre manager.

442
00:51:09,917 --> 00:51:12,417
Madame Leloix's in charge of...

443
00:51:12,584 --> 00:51:14,292
Cultural exchanges.

444
00:51:14,459 --> 00:51:16,001
Tonight's affair.

445
00:51:16,167 --> 00:51:21,084
Our cultural director and his wife.

446
00:51:29,126 --> 00:51:30,792
Why the dinner?

447
00:51:30,959 --> 00:51:33,084
Didn't you know?

448
00:51:33,251 --> 00:51:36,376
Out here we squeeze a celebrity dry,
like a lemon.

449
00:51:36,542 --> 00:51:38,751
I must get my car fixed.

450
00:51:38,917 --> 00:51:40,626
- Will you be long?
- Five minutes!

451
00:51:40,792 --> 00:51:43,751
Okay, I'll keep them busy with the canapГ©s.

452
00:51:45,126 --> 00:51:46,334
Hurry back!

453
00:51:52,751 --> 00:51:55,542
<i>Don't forget my stockings...</i>

454
00:51:55,709 --> 00:51:57,001
<i>Zibeline...</i>

455
00:52:20,751 --> 00:52:22,334
NEAMAT STOCKINGS

456
00:52:39,084 --> 00:52:41,001
- Excuse me.
- I'm sorry, we're closing.

457
00:52:41,167 --> 00:52:43,376
I'd like to buy some stockings.

458
00:52:53,126 --> 00:52:55,667
I bought you two pairs.

459
00:52:55,917 --> 00:52:59,834
There are complications... A dinner for me.

460
00:53:00,001 --> 00:53:03,751
Then I'll eat next door, but stay a while.

461
00:53:03,917 --> 00:53:07,459
Impossible. They're all waiting for me.

462
00:53:07,626 --> 00:53:09,001
All right, never mind.

463
00:53:09,167 --> 00:53:10,667
You understand, don't you?

464
00:53:11,334 --> 00:53:12,584
See you later.

465
00:53:14,959 --> 00:53:16,417
My ticket!

466
00:53:16,584 --> 00:53:19,084
Just buy one at the theatre.

467
00:53:19,251 --> 00:53:20,292
Which one?

468
00:53:20,459 --> 00:53:23,251
- The Capitol, I think.
- But where is it?

469
00:53:23,417 --> 00:53:26,126
Ask the hotel people.

470
00:53:27,542 --> 00:53:29,167
I wonder why I'm here.

471
00:53:46,459 --> 00:53:49,251
- You brought it back?
- They're too busy.

472
00:53:49,417 --> 00:53:52,209
I swear that if it were me... Come on.

473
00:53:52,834 --> 00:53:57,417
You're at the head of the table,
a lady on each side.

474
00:54:01,126 --> 00:54:03,001
Are you married?

475
00:54:03,209 --> 00:54:04,251
I am.

476
00:54:04,459 --> 00:54:06,376
Why isn't your wife with you?

477
00:54:06,834 --> 00:54:08,292
My wife's home.

478
00:54:08,459 --> 00:54:11,334
Oysters or potage, take your choice.

479
00:54:14,251 --> 00:54:15,709
Do you know Reims?

480
00:54:15,792 --> 00:54:16,834
Any children?

481
00:54:17,042 --> 00:54:18,626
A real interview!

482
00:54:19,584 --> 00:54:22,667
I'll answer you one by one.

483
00:54:23,459 --> 00:54:24,834
I have a child.

484
00:54:25,959 --> 00:54:28,334
I've never been here.

485
00:54:28,501 --> 00:54:31,417
And you're leaving tonight?

486
00:54:31,584 --> 00:54:33,751
What about the smile of Reims?

487
00:54:33,917 --> 00:54:37,751
Only AndrГ© Gide could get me
back to the movies.

488
00:54:37,917 --> 00:54:41,126
Last time was to see Charlie Chaplin.

489
00:54:41,876 --> 00:54:45,876
To fix a clock,
he opened it with a can-opener.

490
00:54:46,167 --> 00:54:49,959
I first saw the sea at Paramount.

491
00:54:50,292 --> 00:54:53,542
Last month, we had Daninos.
You know him?

492
00:54:54,042 --> 00:54:56,959
Not personally. How was it?

493
00:54:57,376 --> 00:54:59,167
It was awful!

494
00:54:59,667 --> 00:55:05,084
Everyone was late, it rained,
and my dress was a disaster.

495
00:55:05,751 --> 00:55:07,334
- Was it the colour?
- No.

496
00:55:07,501 --> 00:55:11,959
It made me look terribly fat.
The affair was a real disaster!

497
00:55:12,834 --> 00:55:15,626
Don't worry if our public seems cold,

498
00:55:15,792 --> 00:55:17,209
we never applaud.

499
00:55:18,792 --> 00:55:20,459
Did you know Gide?

500
00:55:20,626 --> 00:55:24,167
- He sells books.
- I also happen to admire Gide.

501
00:55:24,667 --> 00:55:26,542
I met him twice,

502
00:55:26,751 --> 00:55:30,667
the second time, shortly before his death.

503
00:55:30,834 --> 00:55:32,251
Tell us about it.

504
00:55:32,876 --> 00:55:37,876
I'd rather save it for my speech
so as not to repeat myself.

505
00:55:38,417 --> 00:55:39,667
As you like.

506
00:55:42,709 --> 00:55:45,251
A young lady to see you, sir.

507
00:55:49,501 --> 00:55:50,876
Are you sure?

508
00:56:02,042 --> 00:56:06,959
I'm sorry to bother you,
but since I can't stay for your talk,

509
00:56:07,126 --> 00:56:10,626
would you autograph this book for me?

510
00:56:10,792 --> 00:56:12,417
Of course.

511
00:56:13,709 --> 00:56:16,751
My name's Christiane Duchant.

512
00:56:17,792 --> 00:56:19,501
With a that's right.

513
00:56:22,001 --> 00:56:23,459
Thank you very much.

514
00:56:24,251 --> 00:56:26,209
He doesn't let anyone walk over him.

515
00:56:26,376 --> 00:56:30,792
Next year, it'll take us 72
minutes to go to Paris by train.

516
00:56:32,959 --> 00:56:34,292
Excuse me.

517
00:56:46,792 --> 00:56:49,001
I must check the box-office.

518
00:57:06,126 --> 00:57:08,376
Thank you for coming, Mr Lachenay.

519
00:57:08,542 --> 00:57:12,834
Thanks to you, we're sold out.
A rare event in this movie crisis!

520
00:57:13,667 --> 00:57:17,834
Forgive me if I'm blunt,
but I'm a businessman.

521
00:57:18,876 --> 00:57:23,042
Tonight's big turnout isn't for Gide,
it's for you!

522
00:57:23,209 --> 00:57:25,042
They've seen you on TV.

523
00:57:25,209 --> 00:57:27,001
Time to go.

524
00:57:27,167 --> 00:57:29,001
This way.

525
00:57:32,292 --> 00:57:33,876
Take this.

526
00:57:37,751 --> 00:57:40,501
I must leave you now to check the hall.

527
00:57:40,667 --> 00:57:43,501
See you later at the reception.

528
00:57:43,667 --> 00:57:46,459
I'm sorry, I can't stay for it.

529
00:57:46,626 --> 00:57:50,084
I must be back in Paris tonight.

530
00:57:50,251 --> 00:57:53,042
What a pity. Thanks again for coming.

531
00:57:53,209 --> 00:57:55,709
And good luck!

532
00:58:04,459 --> 00:58:06,001
Put your coat down.

533
00:58:10,001 --> 00:58:12,459
