Now, look there.

796
01:20:33,417 --> 01:20:35,084
What do you see?

797
01:20:39,751 --> 01:20:41,001
The same blouse.

798
01:20:41,167 --> 01:20:42,542
Right.

799
01:20:43,334 --> 01:20:44,334
Leopard skin.

800
01:20:47,251 --> 01:20:51,542
Women who wear them like making love.

801
01:21:01,626 --> 01:21:04,626
There's something wrong. What is it?

802
01:21:04,834 --> 01:21:07,001
Nothing.

803
01:21:07,751 --> 01:21:11,709
I know you. I can tell you're worried.

804
01:21:12,126 --> 01:21:13,376
Something I did?

805
01:21:14,917 --> 01:21:16,626
Something I said?

806
01:21:18,376 --> 01:21:19,542
It's awkward...

807
01:21:26,042 --> 01:21:30,292
I know, you've got to call your wife.

808
01:21:31,376 --> 01:21:32,417
That's it.

809
01:21:33,542 --> 01:21:35,667
Couldn't you just say so?

810
01:21:37,334 --> 01:21:38,792
I'll be outside.

811
01:21:39,834 --> 01:21:41,209
Tell me when you're finished.

812
01:21:45,542 --> 01:21:48,126
Connect me with Passy 42-70.

813
01:21:59,209 --> 01:22:01,584
You're all right, Franca?

814
01:22:01,751 --> 01:22:03,001
<i>Yes, and you?</i>

815
01:22:03,167 --> 01:22:06,459
I'm fine, but something came up.

816
01:22:06,626 --> 01:22:10,292
They wanted a repeat performance

817
01:22:10,459 --> 01:22:14,251
so I had to stay over. I'll be home tonight.

818
01:22:15,542 --> 01:22:17,376
<i>You calling from Reims?</i>

819
01:22:17,876 --> 01:22:19,001
Yes, Reims.

820
01:22:19,167 --> 01:22:21,667
<i>Really? I called Reims two nights ago</i>

821
01:22:21,834 --> 01:22:24,709
<i>and was told you'd just left for Paris.</i>

822
01:22:52,334 --> 01:22:54,334
I'll call you tomorrow.

823
01:22:57,292 --> 01:22:58,709
Do you love me?

824
01:23:00,251 --> 01:23:01,292
Yes.

825
01:23:01,626 --> 01:23:03,709
Why won't you say it?

826
01:23:06,584 --> 01:23:10,042
Because you don't like to spell it out,
is that it?

827
01:23:11,667 --> 01:23:13,542
That's it exactly.

828
01:23:19,876 --> 01:23:21,667
Don't forget me.

829
01:24:36,709 --> 01:24:39,792
I know you were with a girl.

830
01:24:41,917 --> 01:24:43,167
Answer me.

831
01:24:45,292 --> 01:24:50,792
Kanayan told me his article
wouldn't be ready in time.

832
01:24:50,959 --> 01:24:53,042
So I called the hotel in Reims,

833
01:24:54,001 --> 01:24:55,792
you'd left the night before.

834
01:24:56,876 --> 01:24:59,751
You were driving, I became frantic.

835
01:24:59,917 --> 01:25:01,251
As if you care!

836
01:25:01,709 --> 01:25:03,584
How could you treat me that way?

837
01:25:03,751 --> 01:25:04,834
Listen, Franca.

838
01:25:04,917 --> 01:25:08,001
Was that asking too much,
a few days with you?

839
01:25:08,334 --> 01:25:11,834
We could have gone off
right after the lecture.

840
01:25:12,417 --> 01:25:14,501
I've waited for five years.

841
01:25:14,667 --> 01:25:16,167
You exaggerate!

842
01:25:16,334 --> 01:25:18,042
No, I've counted them.

843
01:25:18,917 --> 01:25:21,542
I was upset. I needed to be alone.

844
01:25:21,709 --> 01:25:24,167
If you'd only said that to me.

845
01:25:24,334 --> 01:25:27,126
You'd never understand it!

846
01:25:27,292 --> 01:25:28,417
Not so loud.

847
01:25:29,042 --> 01:25:31,209
Sabine never wakes up.

848
01:25:31,626 --> 01:25:33,917
Maybe not, but the nurse is here.

849
01:25:35,167 --> 01:25:38,667
After all, I might want to go out.

850
01:25:39,084 --> 01:25:40,542
I need some fun too!

851
01:25:42,834 --> 01:25:45,084
Franca, I'm tired.

852
01:25:45,251 --> 01:25:48,459
So am I, but it's high time we talked.

853
01:25:50,917 --> 01:25:51,959
Say something!

854
01:25:53,584 --> 01:25:55,459
If I'm wrong, say so.

855
01:25:55,667 --> 01:25:58,334
I'm not up to talking just now.

856
01:25:58,501 --> 01:26:00,334
If there was a woman, tell me.

857
01:26:00,501 --> 01:26:03,167
It would hurt far less if I knew.

858
01:26:03,334 --> 01:26:07,667
- I was alone!
- I don't believe you.

859
01:26:07,834 --> 01:26:09,001
I don't care!

860
01:26:09,167 --> 01:26:10,251
Thanks a lot!

861
01:26:10,542 --> 01:26:13,584
You expect me to be kind? In what way?

862
01:26:13,834 --> 01:26:15,167
Be considerate.

863
01:26:15,334 --> 01:26:17,542
What for? You're not sick.

864
01:26:17,709 --> 01:26:19,417
Yes, thanks to you, I am sick!

865
01:26:20,084 --> 01:26:21,667
I haven't slept in two nights.

866
01:26:28,126 --> 01:26:30,834
Pierre, maybe we should separate.

867
01:26:32,667 --> 01:26:34,376
I'm serious.

868
01:26:35,667 --> 01:26:36,709
All right, I'll go.

869
01:26:45,167 --> 01:26:46,667
I didn't mean all that.

870
01:26:47,459 --> 01:26:49,542
I'm upset. I was nasty.

871
01:26:50,292 --> 01:26:54,209
Look, I propose we try an experiment.

872
01:26:54,584 --> 01:26:58,334
No fighting for a month.
After that we decide.

873
01:26:59,001 --> 01:27:01,126
We've experimented for years.

874
01:27:01,501 --> 01:27:03,709
I won't forgive this.

875
01:27:54,376 --> 01:27:55,501
Hello, Dominique.

876
01:27:56,834 --> 01:27:58,376
Yes, I slept here.

877
01:27:58,917 --> 01:28:02,209
- How did you get your flat?
- The Chaude Agency.

878
01:28:02,376 --> 01:28:05,792
Better call them, I've got to find a flat.

879
01:28:06,459 --> 01:28:08,584
I'm going out for coffee.

880
01:28:10,959 --> 01:28:12,459
Madame Lachenay.

881
01:28:14,126 --> 01:28:15,709
I'll take it in there.

882
01:28:23,126 --> 01:28:24,834
<i>Did you sleep well?</i>

883
01:28:25,251 --> 01:28:27,709
<i>Well, I was up all night.</i>

884
01:28:27,876 --> 01:28:31,584
<i>This is just to thank you
for walking out on me.</i>

885
01:28:31,751 --> 01:28:33,876
<i>I'd forgive anything but that.</i>

886
01:28:34,042 --> 01:28:36,876
<i>Odile's cousin will act as my lawyer.</i>

887
01:28:37,042 --> 01:28:39,417
- As what?
- <i>My divorce lawyer!</i>

888
01:28:39,584 --> 01:28:43,084
<i>I suggest you get someone too.
Why waste time?</i>

889
01:28:43,251 --> 01:28:44,959
<i>I won't be alone long.</i>

890
01:28:45,126 --> 01:28:49,001
<i>Your bags are all packed.
Pick them up any time.</i>

891
01:28:56,667 --> 01:29:01,126
I called your office, but you'd gone.

892
01:29:01,292 --> 01:29:04,417
You can't stay. My father's in town.

893
01:29:04,584 --> 01:29:08,334
He's on his way here.
And I'll be away till Friday.

894
01:29:08,626 --> 01:29:12,667
Let's have dinner Friday.
I've got important news.

895
01:29:13,042 --> 01:29:15,376
Important? Tell me now.

896
01:29:15,542 --> 01:29:18,376
No, you're rushed and this takes time.

897
01:29:18,542 --> 01:29:20,459
Come on,

898
01:29:20,626 --> 01:29:24,667
you tell me you've got big news
and now you won't talk. Tell me.

899
01:29:24,834 --> 01:29:26,834
Nothing doing!

900
01:29:27,001 --> 01:29:30,792
Just tell me if it's something pleasant.

901
01:29:31,501 --> 01:29:35,542
I'm not sure. But it is
serious and important.

902
01:29:35,709 --> 01:29:37,376
What is it?

903
01:29:38,126 --> 01:29:40,834
I meant to explain it properly.
It's just this...

904
01:29:41,751 --> 01:29:46,334
My wife and I are separating
by mutual agreement.

905
01:29:48,876 --> 01:29:50,084
Listen,

906
01:29:50,251 --> 01:29:53,251
there's my dad, you'd better run.
See you Friday.

907
01:29:53,417 --> 01:29:56,542
We won't meet at the airport, but here.

908
01:29:56,709 --> 01:29:57,917
All right.

909
01:30:11,376 --> 01:30:12,584
Excuse me, sir.

910
01:30:20,834 --> 01:30:23,126
- Hello, daddy!
- Hello, darling.

911
01:30:23,292 --> 01:30:24,792
I'm almost ready.

912
01:30:34,959 --> 01:30:37,834
See, I walk like a lady.

913
01:30:54,751 --> 01:30:57,584
My lawyer's waiting to hear from yours.

914
01:30:57,751 --> 01:30:59,459
It's not that urgent.

915
01:30:59,626 --> 01:31:03,376
Yes, it is. I don't like
ambiguous situations.

916
01:31:03,542 --> 01:31:05,417
We can't talk here.

917
01:31:05,584 --> 01:31:08,167
Then let's go to the study.

918
01:31:21,126 --> 01:31:22,459
Sit down.

919
01:31:22,667 --> 01:31:24,334
I'd rather stand.

920
01:31:25,251 --> 01:31:27,167
I'm taking this one.

921
01:31:30,126 --> 01:31:31,667
That one too.

922
01:31:34,042 --> 01:31:36,376
Your bags are ready, they're in the hall.

923
01:31:37,167 --> 01:31:40,001
I didn't know where to send them.

924
01:31:41,209 --> 01:31:42,834
Where do you live?

925
01:31:43,084 --> 01:31:45,042
I sleep in the office.

926
01:31:45,751 --> 01:31:47,917
I plan to take a flat.

927
01:31:48,001 --> 01:31:49,084
You fool!

928
01:31:49,167 --> 01:31:51,417
- Listen Franca!
- I won't listen.

929
01:31:51,792 --> 01:31:55,376
What got into you? Weren't you happy here?

930
01:31:57,959 --> 01:32:00,167
- What's got into you?
- Not in front of the girl.

931
01:32:00,334 --> 01:32:02,667
Now he thinks about her.

932
01:32:03,084 --> 01:32:04,917
Go play with Mademoiselle.

933
01:32:05,209 --> 01:32:07,917
Sabine, go and see Mademoiselle.

934
01:32:08,959 --> 01:32:10,167
Come here, Sabine!

935
01:32:12,292 --> 01:32:14,042
Kanayan called.

936
01:32:14,292 --> 01:32:18,001
I gave him the office number. You were out,

937
01:32:18,751 --> 01:32:20,709
so he rang here.

938
01:32:21,251 --> 01:32:24,584
I told him you weren't living here any more.

939
01:32:25,376 --> 01:32:27,584
What else could I tell him?

940
01:32:27,876 --> 01:32:30,834
The truth. We decided to separate.

941
01:32:31,084 --> 01:32:33,292
We decided to separate!

942
01:32:33,792 --> 01:32:35,876
You'd like me to say that.

943
01:32:36,084 --> 01:32:37,626
Don't count on it.

944
01:32:37,876 --> 01:32:39,959
I'll say that you left me.

945
01:32:40,126 --> 01:32:42,792
Isn't it true? You were fed up?

946
01:32:42,876 --> 01:32:43,959
Calm down, Franca.

947
01:32:44,042 --> 01:32:46,917
You're a louse!

948
01:32:49,209 --> 01:32:50,959
Forgive me, Pierre.

949
01:32:51,584 --> 01:32:55,459
I didn't mean to do that, but I'm so tired.

950
01:32:56,584 --> 01:32:58,542
Come here, sit by me.

951
01:33:01,042 --> 01:33:03,334
I'm sorry for all I said.

952
01:33:04,251 --> 01:33:06,042
You must loathe me.

953
01:33:06,209 --> 01:33:09,376
No Franca, I loathe myself.

954
01:33:10,334 --> 01:33:11,751
Kiss me.

955
01:33:44,209 --> 01:33:45,917
We'll play in your room.

956
01:33:48,334 --> 01:33:50,876
This will go to the cleaner.

957
01:34:20,084 --> 01:34:21,917
I'm taking her out.

958
01:34:22,084 --> 01:34:23,542
Bye, darling.

959
01:34:24,126 --> 01:34:25,584
Bye-bye, daddy.

960
01:34:27,292 --> 01:34:28,917
Come on, we're leaving.

961
01:34:38,084 --> 01:34:39,834
They probably forgot something.

962
01:34:44,042 --> 01:34:46,709
I'd better come back later.

963
01:34:47,292 --> 01:34:50,042
No, stay here. Anyway, Pierre's leaving.

964
01:34:52,209 --> 01:34:53,792
I must be going.

965
01:34:53,959 --> 01:34:56,042
Call me tonight. I'd like that.

966
01:34:56,209 --> 01:34:58,167
Really?

967
01:34:58,667 --> 01:35:03,126
You got some Champagne from Reims.

968
01:35:03,876 --> 01:35:06,167
Just keep it in the cellar.

969
01:35:09,751 --> 01:35:11,626
Here's the Foujita.

970
01:35:12,001 --> 01:35:14,084
What for? I gave it to you.

971
01:35:14,251 --> 01:35:15,709
Take it back.

972
01:35:15,876 --> 01:35:18,334
I don't want it, it's yours. Keep it.

973
01:35:26,709 --> 01:35:29,709
Want to come back for supper, or to sleep,

974
01:35:31,001 --> 01:35:32,626
or just for supper?

975
01:35:32,792 --> 01:35:37,417
It won't work, you know,
with all that's happened.

976
01:35:50,167 --> 01:35:54,209
I'm sorry, Odile.
I can't go with you, I don't feel well.

977
01:35:55,709 --> 01:35:57,417
What a fool I am!

978
01:35:57,584 --> 01:35:59,792
I should have known better.

979
01:35:59,959 --> 01:36:02,209
What's Pierre done to you?

980
01:36:02,376 --> 01:36:04,084
What did he want?

981
01:36:07,751 --> 01:36:09,876
That's what he wanted!

982
01:36:19,626 --> 01:36:23,209
Top luxury apartment block
Ready for AUTUMN 64

983
01:36:23,376 --> 01:36:26,292
Franca, you've got to calm down.

984
01:36:26,459 --> 01:36:28,501
You need some sleep.

985
01:36:29,751 --> 01:36:31,459
Let me have a sleeping pill?

986
01:36:39,209 --> 01:36:41,334
You said you'd be right down.

987
01:36:41,501 --> 01:36:45,251
I'd better stay.
Franca's very upset over Pierre.

988
01:36:45,334 --> 01:36:48,751
I'm afraid she might do something foolish.

989
01:37:14,959 --> 01:37:19,292
In the plane today, we ran into a storm.

990
01:37:19,459 --> 01:37:22,584
One of the passengers,
an American, was scared.

991
01:37:22,667 --> 01:37:25,917
He drank so much whisky,

992
01:37:26,001 --> 01:37:30,459
he went berserk.
He drove us all crazy, it was real wild!

993
01:37:30,626 --> 01:37:33,751
Don't talk so loud, people are staring.

994
01:37:34,584 --> 01:37:36,584
You're charming tonight.

995
01:37:39,667 --> 01:37:41,334
Did your dad enjoy Paris?

996
01:37:46,292 --> 01:37:48,001
Did he have a good time?

997
01:37:49,376 --> 01:37:50,667
I don't know.

998
01:37:51,126 --> 01:37:53,251
I'm tired. Please take me home.

999
01:37:54,334 --> 01:37:57,876
Why? The programme starts in 10 minutes.

1000
01:37:59,959 --> 01:38:01,334
Take me home.

1001
01:38:02,209 --> 01:38:04,167
You were so eager to come here.

1002
01:38:05,751 --> 01:38:08,959
Well, now I'm tired. I leave tomorrow.

1003
01:38:11,001 --> 01:38:12,084
Mad at me?

1004
01:38:15,334 --> 01:38:16,376
You're sure?

1005
01:38:18,042 --> 01:38:19,876
Positive.

1006
01:38:26,709 --> 01:38:31,542
I wasn't very good company, I know,
but you must understand,

1007
01:38:31,834 --> 01:38:34,251
I've had a pretty rough week.

1008
01:38:34,459 --> 01:38:36,792
Franca, the separation...

1009
01:38:36,959 --> 01:38:40,917
I thought you both wanted this separation.

1010
01:38:41,417 --> 01:38:43,459
Yes, of course,

1011
01:38:44,542 --> 01:38:47,334
but it's not so easy after 15 years.

1012
01:38:47,667 --> 01:38:49,209
You told her about me?

1013
01:38:49,376 --> 01:38:53,792
No. I thought the later, the better.

1014
01:38:54,084 --> 01:38:55,501
I don't agree.

1015
01:38:55,667 --> 01:39:00,709
If it was me, I'd prefer the
truth even if it's another girl.

1016
01:39:01,584 --> 01:39:03,126
You know the score.

1017
01:39:03,292 --> 01:39:05,209
I didn't see it that way.

1018
01:39:05,751 --> 01:39:07,376
Speaking as a man,

1019
01:39:07,542 --> 01:39:10,667
I tell you, it's a mistake.

1020
01:39:12,459 --> 01:39:17,417
You may be right.
I'll tell her, but it won't be easy.

1021
01:39:18,792 --> 01:39:21,126
You see, it's been hard on me too,

1022
01:39:22,001 --> 01:39:23,834
harder than I thought.

1023
01:39:24,334 --> 01:39:26,042
We're used to each other,

1024
01:39:27,417 --> 01:39:30,876
and there's Sabine.
I'll miss seeing her every day.

1025
01:39:32,209 --> 01:39:35,459
If that's how it is, you sure goofed!

1026
01:39:37,501 --> 01:39:40,876
You can give Sabine
some calves liver for lunch...

1027
01:39:41,126 --> 01:39:43,917
I'll get the door!
And some mashed potatoes.

1028
01:39:46,209 --> 01:39:48,584
The suit from the cleaner's.

1029
01:39:48,751 --> 01:39:50,126
Hold on.

1030
01:39:52,917 --> 01:39:56,501
We found this stub in the pocket.

1031
01:39:56,667 --> 01:39:58,376
Thank you.

1032
01:40:05,792 --> 01:40:07,209
PHOTO ENLARGEMENT

1033
01:40:16,959 --> 01:40:20,001
This is the living room.

1034
01:40:22,626 --> 01:40:25,542
There, my study and the library.

1035
01:40:27,917 --> 01:40:30,376
That will be our room,

1036
01:40:31,459 --> 01:40:33,501
with Sabine's next to it
for when she visits us.

1037
01:40:33,667 --> 01:40:36,376
I'll get an extra room for the nanny.

1038
01:40:39,876 --> 01:40:41,542
So you want to marry me?

1039
01:40:42,334 --> 01:40:45,876
If I say yes, you'll talk to my father.
Is that it?

1040
01:40:48,542 --> 01:40:50,042
Listen to me,

1041
01:40:51,376 --> 01:40:54,792
I've discovered some facts of life lately.

1042
01:40:55,417 --> 01:40:57,584
There's a misunderstanding.

1043
01:40:58,084 --> 01:41:00,042
When you looked me up in Paris,

1044
01:41:00,126 --> 01:41:04,876
I was pleased because
I thought you might misjudge me

1045
01:41:05,042 --> 01:41:07,167
after what happened in Lisbon.

1046
01:41:09,084 --> 01:41:11,792
On the way here, I guessed...

1047
01:41:13,334 --> 01:41:17,084
But now that it's out, I've got to speak up.

1048
01:41:18,792 --> 01:41:22,626
It's just as well you brought it to a head...

1049
01:41:22,792 --> 01:41:24,626
it was all happening too quickly.

1050
01:41:25,751 --> 01:41:31,751
Because it just would have dragged on
to wind up the same way.

1051
01:41:32,626 --> 01:41:34,292
What's the point?

1052
01:41:35,542 --> 01:41:37,626
In the restaurant last night,

1053
01:41:37,792 --> 01:41:41,376
I irritated you, I could tell.

1054
01:41:41,709 --> 01:41:43,376
You almost hated me.

1055
01:41:43,542 --> 01:41:44,542
It's true.

1056
01:41:47,209 --> 01:41:50,709
To plan a wedding when you reach
that point, it makes no sense!

1057
01:41:53,209 --> 01:41:56,459
I know you're hurt. I feel bad, too.

1058
01:42:00,126 --> 01:42:05,792
If you'd like, we could
meet from time to time.

1059
01:42:13,417 --> 01:42:15,251
I'm truly sorry.

1060
01:42:17,751 --> 01:42:19,084
Bye, Pierre.

1061
01:43:34,042 --> 01:43:36,084
- How much is it?
- 14 francs.

1062
01:44:35,126 --> 01:44:37,209
Need some help?

1063
01:44:37,376 --> 01:44:40,334
How about a little walk?

1064
01:44:41,834 --> 01:44:44,042
Why hurry home?

1065
01:44:53,209 --> 01:44:56,917
We can go to a cafГ© or up to my place.

1066
01:44:57,209 --> 01:44:59,251
Who the hell are you?

1067
01:44:59,417 --> 01:45:01,292
What are you after?

1068
01:45:01,459 --> 01:45:05,876
Do all women go for you?
You take them to the country?

1069
01:45:06,042 --> 01:45:09,709
Irresistible, a Don Juan...

1070
01:45:09,876 --> 01:45:12,542
God's gift to women?

1071
01:45:13,001 --> 01:45:16,042
Ever take a good look at yourself?

1072
01:45:16,209 --> 01:45:17,876
Come and have a look.

1073
01:45:18,084 --> 01:45:19,667
- Look again!
- Leave me alone!

1074
01:45:41,959 --> 01:45:44,292
Take Sabine to Madame Odile's.

1075
01:45:44,459 --> 01:45:47,209
Look Mummy, I've finished it all off!

1076
01:45:47,376 --> 01:45:49,251
After her homework?

1077
01:45:49,417 --> 01:45:51,126
No, right after she eats.

1078
01:45:51,292 --> 01:45:52,626
And the homework?

1079
01:45:53,292 --> 01:45:55,459
She'll do it at Madame Odile's.

1080
01:45:55,626 --> 01:45:56,667
All right, Madame.

1081
01:48:23,042 --> 01:48:24,626
A token, please.

1082
01:48:48,084 --> 01:48:49,126
Odile?

1083
01:48:52,626 --> 01:48:54,876
I want to thank you for everything.

1084
01:48:55,209 --> 01:48:58,084
I'm off for a rest tomorrow.

1085
01:48:58,959 --> 01:49:01,959
Ask Franca, can I see Sabine before I go?

1086
01:49:02,126 --> 01:49:05,751
<i>As you wish, Pierre. But it's such a mess.</i>

1087
01:49:08,167 --> 01:49:10,334
What can I do about it now?

1088
01:49:11,001 --> 01:49:12,542
It's too late.

1089
01:49:14,751 --> 01:49:17,751
Since you'll be seeing her,

1090
01:49:18,959 --> 01:49:20,167
would you let me know?

1091
01:49:20,584 --> 01:49:22,334
Let you know what?

1092
01:49:24,209 --> 01:49:27,167
If you can still change your mind?

1093
01:49:28,584 --> 01:49:32,042
If you really want to go back to Franca,

1094
01:49:32,334 --> 01:49:35,876
<i>I'm sure she'd agree if you ask her yourself.</i>

1095
01:49:36,042 --> 01:49:38,376
You may be right, Odile.

1096
01:49:39,959 --> 01:49:41,459
I'll do it next week.

1097
01:49:41,626 --> 01:49:45,542
<i>Why? The sooner the better.
Call her right now.</i>

1098
01:49:45,709 --> 01:49:47,001
Now?

1099
01:49:47,709 --> 01:49:51,126
I'd rather wait awhile.

1100
01:49:51,292 --> 01:49:55,626
<i>What for?
Do you think she'll sit around for 10 years?</i>

1101
01:49:57,001 --> 01:50:00,209
<i>Pierre, I beg you, don't put it off.</i>

1102
01:50:00,751 --> 01:50:02,917
You're probably right.

1103
01:50:04,751 --> 01:50:06,376
I guess I'll do that.

1104
01:50:17,376 --> 01:50:18,776
- Another token, please.
- One more?

1105
01:50:18,917 --> 01:50:20,292
That's right.

1106
01:51:45,584 --> 01:51:46,709
I'm going out.

1107
01:51:46,876 --> 01:51:48,709
Will you lunch here?

1108
01:51:48,959 --> 01:51:50,834
No, I'm not eating here.

1109
01:52:31,042 --> 01:52:32,959
Madame Lachenay's place.

1110
01:52:34,542 --> 01:52:36,334
Is this you, Mademoiselle?

1111
01:52:37,001 --> 01:52:40,209
- My wife, please.
- <i>She just this minute went out.</i>

1112
01:52:42,042 --> 01:52:44,126
Look in the hall.

1113
01:52:44,709 --> 01:52:47,126
Hold on, sir. I'll see.

1114
01:53:00,167 --> 01:53:02,376
No, she's left the house.

1115
01:53:02,542 --> 01:53:06,376
<i>Then she's in the street.
Call her from the window.</i>

1116
01:53:06,542 --> 01:53:08,209
I'll have a look.

1117
01:53:39,084 --> 01:53:43,876
I'm sorry, but her car just pulled out.
Any message?

1118
01:53:44,417 --> 01:53:48,792
Tell her that I phoned and
will call back later.

1119
01:53:48,959 --> 01:53:50,667
<i>I'll tell her, sir.</i>

1120
01:53:50,834 --> 01:53:51,876
That's all.

1121
01:56:49,459 --> 01:56:52,042
Call the police!

